HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1009
By Barrett
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Poppy Pewitt,
Tennessee Golf Association's 2025 Girls' Junior
Player of the Year.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should salute those
student athletes who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as true
champions of whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such exemplary young athlete is Poppy Pewitt, who was recently
named the Tennessee Golf Association's 2025 Girls' Junior Player of the Year; and
WHEREAS, a sophomore at Dickson County High School, Ms. Pewitt had an amazing
season that culminated in her winning the TSSAA Class AA individual girls' golf state
championship; and
WHEREAS, she also helped the Dickson County Lady Cougars qualify for the state
tournament, a feat that had not been achieved by the program since 1985; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Pewitt won this year's Tennessee Girls' Junior Championship in an
exciting three-hole playoff; and
WHEREAS, Poppy Pewitt epitomizes all that is good in today's student athlete, as she
has achieved a premier level of success in competition while exhibiting the highest degree of
character in all aspects of life; and
WHEREAS, her display of drive and determination on the golf course surely bodes well
for her future success, and her accomplishments are a tremendous source of pride for her
family, her school, and her community; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Pewitt's ability, success, and dedication to excellence make her a fine
ambassador for all Tennessee student athletes, and she should be specially recognized; now,
therefore,
HJR1009
013773
- 1 -

BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we recognize and honor Poppy Pewitt upon being named Tennessee Golf
Association's 2025 Girls' Junior Player of the Year and extend to her our best wishes for every
continued success in all her future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
